The paper deals with deep neural networks and their statistical characteristics, which are relevant to the performance and interpretability of deep learning. The focus is on classification tasks, which suggests that the paper could belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) or Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. However, the paper also discusses the design of regularizers for shaping DNN representations, which is a common topic in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper presents experimental results on popular benchmark datasets, which suggests that it could also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Overall, cs.LG is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.CL.
